[32m+[m[32m/**[m
[32m+[m[32m * One-shot post-migration pass that normalises the persisted queue:[m
[32m+[m[32m *[m
[32m+[m[32m *   1. Multiple entries with the same session_id → merged into the first[m
[32m+[m[32m *      (chunks concatenated, then deduped in step 2; offsets / closed /[m
[32m+[m[32m *      completed flags merged with max/OR).[m
[32m+[m[32m *   2. Within each entry, chunks with the same chunk_index AND the same[m
[32m+[m[32m *      hash → keep ONE (prefer status='uploaded', else first); drop the[m
[32m+[m[32m *      rest.[m
[32m+[m[32m *   3. Within each entry, chunks with the same chunk_index but DIFFERENT[m
[32m+[m[32m *      hash → the recorded bytes diverged. We cannot guess which is[m
[32m+[m[32m *      right, so we mark EVERY chunk in that entry as `failed` with code[m
[32m+[m[32m *      `CORRUPT_HASH_DIVERGENCE` and let the worker finalise the session[m
[32m+[m[32m *      via the existing all-settled path. Nothing is uploaded blindly.[m
[32m+[m[32m *[m
[32m+[m[32m * Idempotent: running it again on a clean queue is a no-op.[m
[32m+[m[32m *[m
